verbs.description: Since President Trump [V: has] endorsed and is already campaigning for the top Republican candidate in Missouri 's primary race for the U.S. Senate , most of the state 's GOP voters have at this point filed behind Attorney General Josh Hawley as the best bet for toppling incumbent Senator Claire McCaskill ( D - Mo . ) . Hawley 's resume is impressive : He 's a Yale grad . He 's a Harvard grad . He 's argued for religious freedom in front of the United States Supreme Court . He was previously a Constitutional law professor . And he ai n't ugly , making him even tougher to beat by those who dare try . Amongst the GOP field of ten candidates in the primary , the two who stand the best chance at challenging Hawley are Austin Petersen and Tony Monetti . They 've raised over $ 400,000 and $ 300,000 respectively , a pittance compared to Hawley 's coffer of more than $ 3 million , and amounts completely dwarfed by McCaskill 's anticipated $ 25 million haul .
